Package com.tractrac.model.lib.api.event

Interface IRaceCompetitor

All Superinterfaces:
IMetadataContainer, IPropertiesContainer, com.tractrac.util.lib.api.serialize.ISerializable
public interface IRaceCompetitor extends IMetadataContainer, com.tractrac.util.lib.api.serialize.ISerializable

Encapsulates data related to a specific Competitor of a specific Race.

A race competitor is linked to a Competitor and a Race. Furthermore, it may be linked to a Route, and have an individual start time.

Author:
Jesper Grooss

    • getStatus

      RaceCompetitorStatusType getStatus()
      Gets the current competitor status. It will be one of these values:
      • FINISHING
      • DISQUALIFIED
      • ABANDONED
      • RETIRED
      • NO_DATA: No data
      • DONT_RACE: Don't race today
      Returns:
      competitor status.

    • getStatusTime

      long getStatusTime()

      When the status is one of: ABANDONED, RETIRED or DISQUALIFIED it contains when the competitor has changed to this state.

      If this value is 0L means that this value has not been established.

      Returns:
      Date when the current status became active.

    • getStatusLastChangedTime

      long getStatusLastChangedTime()

      Gets the time stamp when the race competitor status returned by {this.getStatus} was updated

      The value is assigned when the race competitor is created and it can't be null (0L)
